shaw, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Bradshaw Hall, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bradshaw","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the three places called Bradshaw in Lancashire, Yorkshire, and Derbyshire, from Old English <i>brād</i> ‘broad’ + <i>sceaga</i> ‘thicket’."],"variants":[{"name":"Brayshaw","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): variant of   Bradshaw  , reflecting the local Yorkshire pronunciation."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Henry Bradshaw was born in 1335, in Bradshaw, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert De Bradshaw, was 35 and his mother, Margaret Dacre, was 30. He married Alice Rivington in 1355, in Bradshaw, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1395, in Marple, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1335–1395":"1335–1395","1326–Male":"1326–Surnud","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1358–1403":"1358–1403","1362–1420":"1362–1420","1300–1362":"1300–1362","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1305":"1305","1403":"1403","1326":"1326","1358":"1358","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1420":"1420","1362":"1362","1395":"1395","1 June 1362":"1. juuni 1362","Bolton